The Deputy President of the Senate, Ovie Omo-Agege, on Thursday formally declared to contest the governorship election in Delta State on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC).
Deputy Senate President Omo-Agege made the declaration in Effurun, Uvwie Local Council Area.
Omo-Agege represents Delta North Senatorial District in the National Assembly.
The deputy senate president is leading a faction of the APC in Delta State while the Minister of State for Labour, Festus Keyamo SAN, is leading another APC faction.
